commit.message:
Do not test against conda in GitHub automatic tests

Latest Spyder version on conda-forge is 6.0.0alpha2 at the moment.
That is not compatible with Spyder's master branch.

Test against Python 3.9-3.11 in GitHub automatic tests

We used to test against Python 3.8-3.10, but conda-forge is dropping
support for Python 3.8.

Update config page test to new API

* Return value of `.create_checkbox()` changed in spyder-ide/spyder#20926
  (Show tooltips in Preferences).
* Handling of Prefs dialog box size changed in spyder-ide/spyder#21233
  (Improve style of Preferences dialog box).

Update to plugin API from Spyder 6.0.0a2

Specifically, make `UnitTestPlugin.get_description()` a static method
and `UnitTestPlugin.get_icon()` a class method.
Add functionality to save and load command-line args.

commit.message: Fix path manipulations on Windows
Run single test using nose2
Run single test using unittest
Run single test using pytest
Pass single test request on to test runners

Add "Run only this test" to context menu of datatree

At the moment, this action is passed on to the UnitTestWidget, but it
simply runs all tests.

Use test names relative to wdir, not rootdir

Before the introduction of PyTestWorker, test names were taken from the
output of `pytest -v` and those names are relative to wdir. After, the
plugin displayed node ids which are relative to the pytest root dir.
This adds unnecessary information if the root dir is a parent of wdir,
so this commit reverts back to the earlier behaviour.
Move helper functions inside PyTestRunner class
Add type annotations to files in backend directory

Remove references to dark interface setting

After commit 4d6e49db, the correct colours for dark/light interface are
chosen automatically inside Spyder proper, so we don't need any special
handling in the plugin.
Remove unused imports

Remove attribute executable in class RunnerBase

This attribute is no longer used after commit f61c5a52.
